<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78d74056-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s943b"><num value="943b">§ 943b.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id78d74057-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s943b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior, acting through the Director of the United States Fish and Wildlife Service.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id78d74058-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s943b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> “Great Lakes fish and wildlife” means fauna, fish, and invertebrates dependent on Great Lakes resources, and located within the Great Lakes Basin.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id78d74059-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/102/440/tII/s204">Pub. L. 102–440, title II, § 204</ref>, <date date="1992-10-23">Oct. 23, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/2233">106 Stat. 2233</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
